                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <head>No. 11.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Carrié</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-08-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 5, 1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 28th ultimo, conveying the gratifying intelligence of the
                    signing of a treaty between the Argentine Republic and Chili, whereby the long
                    disputed boundary question is permanently settled. This government rejoices with
                    its sister republics of the far south in so happy an event, and trusts that the
                    harmonious relations now established between them may remain unbroken.</p>
                <p>Accept, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
